(23, 'national-holidays-and-festivals', 'NATIONAL HOLIDAYS AND FESTIVALS', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'NATIONAL HOLIDAYS AND FESTIVALS', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '                <div class="template-1">\r\n                                    <div class="container">\r\n                                       <div class="item">\r\n                                          <div class="row">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-7 col-sm-12 com-xs-12" contenteditable="false">\r\n                                                <h2>May 9</h2>\r\n                                                <p>May 9 is a triple holiday - the Day of Victory in the Great Patriotic War (the Armenians of Artsakh were directly involved in World War II), Shoushi Liberation Day and Foundation Day of the Defense Army of Artsakh. The military parade is held in the Renaissance Square, events and a variety of cultural and sporting events is hosted. </p>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-5 col-sm-12 com-xs-12">\r\n                                               <div class="img-block">\r\n                                                   <img data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal" data-title="Feedback" src="http://storage.loc/web/img/about/National%20holdays%20and%20festivals.jpg" alt="Hyunot" title="Hyunot">\r\n                                               </div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                          </div>\r\n                                       </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="template-1">\r\n                                    <div class="container">\r\n                                       <div class="item">\r\n                                          <div class="row">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-7 col-sm-12 com-xs-12" contenteditable="false">\r\n                                                <h2>Independence Day<br></h2>\r\n                                                <p>Independence Day (September 2) is considered one of the most solemn holidays. Festive events are held throughout the country. Every year on September 2nd in Renaissance Square is held a gala-concert with the participation of local and guest artists from Armenia and abroad. The holiday ends with fireworks.  </p>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-5 col-sm-12 com-xs-12">\r\n                                               <div class="img-block">\r\n                                                   <img data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal" data-title="Feedback" src="http://storage.loc/web/img/about/26177150_875269875986928_1692196599_n.jpg" alt="Hyunot" title="Hyunot">\r\n                                               </div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                          </div>\r\n                                       </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="template-1">\r\n                                    <div class="container">\r\n                                       <div class="item">\r\n                                          <div class="row">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-7 col-sm-12 com-xs-12" contenteditable="false">\r\n                                                <h2>Mulberry Festival</h2>\r\n                                                <p>Mulberry Festival: Every year on the third Saturday of June Mulberry (Toot) festival is held near Amaras monastery (Martouni region of NKR. Mulberry festival is considered to be one of the most popular events in Karabakh. It is held only one day, and during the whole event guests have the opportunity to taste and buy homemade vodka, doshab, dried mulberry etc. Artsakh skillful cookers are presenting methods and traditions of preparing doshab and mulberry vodka. </p>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-5 col-sm-12 com-xs-12">\r\n                                               <div class="img-block">\r\n                                                   <img data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal" data-title="Feedback" src="http://storage.loc/web/img/regions/festivals/Mulberry.jpg" alt="Hyunot" title="Mulberry">\r\n                                               </div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                          </div>\r\n                                       </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="template-1">\r\n                                    <div class="container">\r\n                                       <div class="item">\r\n                                          <div class="row">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-7 col-sm-12 com-xs-12" contenteditable="false">\r\n                                                <h2>Tnjre<br></h2>\r\n                                                <p>The “Tnjre” international classical music festival of young performers gathers famous and young musicians from Karabakh and all over the world in June.  During the festival famous musicians from Germany, Italy, Finland, Netherlands and other countries organize master classes of piano, violin and clarinet for the inhabitants and guests of Artsakh. Concerts are held in the capital city and regional centers during the festival. </p>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-5 col-sm-12 com-xs-12">\r\n                                               <div class="img-block">\r\n                                                   <img data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal" data-title="Feedback" src="http://storage.loc/web/img/regions/festivals/tnjri.jpg" alt="Hyunot" title="tnjri">\r\n                                               </div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                          </div>\r\n                                       </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="template-1">\r\n                                    <div class="container">\r\n                                       <div class="item">\r\n                                          <div class="row">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-7 col-sm-12 com-xs-12" contenteditable="false">\r\n                                                <h2>Harvest fair<br></h2>\r\n                                                <p>Harvest fair. The second Sunday of October is celebrated as the Day of Agriculture. Every year a Harvest Festival is organized this day  in the Stepanakert Renaissance Square.  More than 200 vendors from all the regions of Artsakh introduce their production to the thousands of visitors that attended the fair.  </p>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-5 col-sm-12 com-xs-12">\r\n                                               <div class="img-block">\r\n                                                   <img data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal" data-title="Feedback" src="http://storage.loc/web/img/regions/harvest.jpg" alt="Hyunot" title="Hyunot">\r\n                                               </div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                          </div>\r\n                                       </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                   